data.title: Constitutional Monarchy - Vocab, Definition, and Must Know Facts
data.meta_description: A Constitutional Monarchy is a form of government where a king or queen acts as Head of State within parameters set by a constitution. They have ceremonial duties rather than governing responsibilities.
data.text:
Definition

A Constitutional Monarchy is a form of government where a king or queen acts as Head of State within parameters set by a constitution. They have ceremonial duties rather than governing responsibilities.
